import re

def parse_syntax(syntax):
    operations = re.findall('', syntax)
    names = re.findall("name\\|\\'([^\\']*)\\'", syntax)
    newlines = syntax.count("nl|'\\n'")
    strings = re.findall("string\\|\\'([^\\']*)\\'", syntax)
    return {'operations': operations, 'names': names, 'newlines': newlines, 'strings': strings}
